{"type":"message","id":"7d3ef4e1","parentId":"ad71d6c2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T03:08:03.985Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_znyqrre5mj1x_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: \"stock_analyzer\"\ndescription: \"分析股票和市场。当用户想要分析单个或多个股票，或进行市场复盘时调用。\"\n---\n\n# 股票分析器\n\n本技能基于 `analyzer_service.py` 的逻辑，提供分析股票和整体市场的功能。\n\n## 输出结构 (`AnalysisResult`)\n\n分析函数返回一个 `AnalysisResult` 对象（或其列表），该对象具有丰富的结构。以下是其关键组件的简要概述，并附有真实的输出示例：\n\n`dashboard` 属性包含核心分析，分为四个主要部分：\n1.  **`core_conclusion`**: 一句话总结、信号类型和仓位建议。\n2.  **`data_perspective`**: 技术数据，包括趋势状态、价格位置、量能分析和筹码结构。\n3.  **`intelligence`**: 定性信息，如新闻、风险警报和积极催化剂。\n4.  **`battle_plan`**: 可操作的策略，包括狙击点（买/卖目标）、仓位策略和风险控制清单。\n\n## 配置 (`Config`)\n\n所有分析函数都可以接受一个可选的 `config` 对象。该对象包含应用程序的所有配置，例如 API 密钥、通知设置和分析参数。\n\n如果未提供 `config` 对象，函数将自动使用从 `.env` 文件加载的全局单例实例。\n\n**参考:** [`Config`](src/config.py)\n\n## 函数\n\n### 1. 分析单只股票"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"---\nname: \"stock_analyzer\"\ndescription: \"分析股票和市场。当用户想要分析单个或多个股票，或进行市场复盘时调用。\"\n---\n\n# 股票分析器\n\n本技能基于 `analyzer_service.py` 的逻辑，提供分析股票和整体市场的功能。\n\n## 输出结构 (`AnalysisResult`)\n\n分析函数返回一个 `AnalysisResult` 对象（或其列表），该对象具有丰富的结构。以下是其关键组件的简要概述，并附有真实的输出示例：\n\n`dashboard` 属性包含核心分析，分为四个主要部分：\n1.  **`core_conclusion`**: 一句话总结、信号类型和仓位建议。\n2.  **`data_perspective`**: 技术数据，包括趋势状态、价格位置、量能分析和筹码结构。\n3.  **`intelligence`**: 定性信息，如新闻、风险警报和积极催化剂。\n4.  **`battle_plan`**: 可操作的策略，包括狙击点（买/卖目标）、仓位策略和风险控制清单。\n\n## 配置 (`Config`)\n\n所有分析函数都可以接受一个可选的 `config` 对象。该对象包含应用程序的所有配置，例如 API 密钥、通知设置和分析参数。\n\n如果未提供 `config` 对象，函数将自动使用从 `.env` 文件加载的全局单例实例。\n\n**参考:** [`Config`](src/config.py)\n\n## 函数\n\n### 1. 分析单只股票","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace-coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775358483982}}
{"type":"message","id":"727dbfd9","parentId":"7d3ef4e1","timestamp":"2026-04-05T03:08:12.402Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The local repo already has a SKILL.md and is a full-featured application. The clawhub skill is a packaged version of a similar skill. The user wants to merge the clawhub skill updates into their local repo.\n\nLet me check what's different between the local SKILL.md and the clawhub one. But more importantly, I should:\n1. First check git status of the local repo (it's clean)\n2. Fetch latest from GitHub origin\n3. Then install the clawhub skill to see what files need to be merged\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The user likely has been developing locally and also wants to incorporate the latest changes from the clawhub skill `stock-daily-analysis`. The merge would involve:\n1. Fetching latest from GitHub (origin)\n2. Installing clawhub skill to a temp location and comparing its files with the local repo\n3. Merging any updates\n\nLet me do this step by step.","thinkingSignature":"04bcb9c86ad909b800d6c2e0f3f9c6846b2dc6ebba756d4fe0ca2a6db7ad24e6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6yibvf6xkiu3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/daily_stock_analysis && git fetch origin && git log origin/main --oneline -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6yibvf6xkiu3_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/daily_stock_analysis && git diff HEAD origin/main --stat | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9118,"output":276,"cacheRead":21619,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31013,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775358483985,"responseId":"062105160e915276c3b202f6b8d967a8"}}
